results.name: a(n) = cardinality of a certain set of natural numbers defined using A117818.
comment: Let s(n) = A117818(n). Define sets C_n of natural numbers by C_0 = {1}; C_(n+1) = C_n union {s(x+y): x, y in C_n} for n >= 0. Then a(n) = |C_n|.
reference: Mihai Caragiu, P. A. Vicol. M. Kaki, On Conway's subprime function, a covering of N and an unexpected appearance of the golden ratio, Fib. Q., to appear, 2017.
results.author: _N. J. A. Sloane_, Sep 29 2017
